        "type": "tool_result",
        "content": "     1→[\n     2→  {\n     3→    \"title\": \"Karpathy Introduces 'Claw' - New AI Architecture Layer Above LLM Agents\",\n     4→    \"description\": \"Andrej Karpathy coined a new term 'Claw' as a conceptual layer above LLM Agents, forming a framework: Chat → Code → Claw. The tweet received 1.7 million views within 24 hours. Similar to how 'Vibe Coding' became widely adopted, 'Claw' may become a new industry term. This reflects the evolving understanding of AI system architectures and how different components interact.\",\n     5→    \"author\": \"Andrej Karpathy\",\n     6→    \"source\": \"Twitter\",\n     7→    \"url\": \"https://blog.csdn.net/weixin_40774379/article/details/158313699\",\n     8→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-22\",\n     9→    \"topics\": [\"AI architecture\", \"LLM agents\", \"conceptual frameworks\", \"Claw\", \"Vibe Coding\"],\n    10→    \"type\": \"opinion\"\n    11→  },\n    12→  {\n    13→    \"title\": \"Karpathy's AI-Assisted Programming Workflow Shift: 80% AI + 20% Manual\",\n    14→    \"description\": \"Andrej Karpathy revealed his workflow has dramatically shifted from 80% manual coding + 20% AI assistance to 80% AI + 20% manual editing. He uses tools like Claude Code, Codex, and Cursor to rebuild products from scratch. One company reported 10-20x faster progress using these AI coding tools, demonstrating the transformative impact of AI on software development workflows.\",\n    15→    \"author\": \"Andrej Karpathy\",\n    16→    \"source\": \"Twitter\",\n    17→    \"url\": \"https://blog.csdn.net/weixin_40774379/article/details/158313699\",\n    18→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-22\",\n    19→    \"topics\": [\"AI-assisted coding\", \"workflow transformation\", \"Claude Code\", \"Cursor\", \"developer productivity\"],\n    20→    \"type\": \"opinion\"\n    21→  },\n    22→  {\n    23→    \"title\": \"Custom Application Development in 1 Hour: 'The Era of App Stores is Ending'\",\n    24→    \"description\": \"Karpathy built a personalized fitness tracking dashboard in just 1 hour using 'vibe coding' - a task that would have taken 10 hours two years ago. He made the bold prediction that 'The era of app stores is ending,' arguing that LLMs can generate hundreds of lines of code in seconds for highly customized, on-demand applications. LLMs are like a new operating system, with the context window serving as RAM.\",\n    25→    \"author\": \"Andrej Karpathy\",\n    26→    \"source\": \"Twitter\",\n    27→    \"url\": \"https://blog.csdn.net/weixin_40774379/article/details/158313699\",\n    28→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-19\",\n    29→    \"topics\": [\"vibe coding\", \"custom applications\", \"app stores\", \"LLM as OS\", \"context windows\"],\n    30→    \"type\": \"opinion\"\n    31→  },\n    32→  {\n    33→    \"title\": \"Gemini 3.1 Pro Release: Karpathy Declares 'App Store Era Over'\",\n    34→    \"description\": \"Following the release of Gemini 3.1 Pro with Tsinghua's Yao Shunyu endorsing it, Andrej Karpathy reiterated that 'The application store era is ending.' This sparked debate and criticism from some developers who argued that app stores still provide value in discovery, security, and monetization. The discussion highlights the tension between AI-generated on-demand software and traditional app distribution models.\",\n    35→    \"author\": \"Andrej Karpathy\",\n    36→    \"source\": \"Twitter\",\n    37→    \"url\": \"https://m.huxiu.com/article/4835899.html\",\n    38→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-23\",\n    39→    \"topics\": [\"Gemini 3.1 Pro\", \"app stores\", \"AI-generated software\", \"distribution models\"],\n    40→    \"type\": \"opinion\"\n    41→  },\n    42→  {\n    43→    \"title\": \"Simon Willison's 2026 AI Predictions: LLM-Generated Code No Longer 'Garbage'\",\n    44→    \"description\": \"Simon Willison, Django co-founder, published predictions for AI technology trends. By end of 2026, he predicts claiming LLM-generated code is 'garbage' will no longer be defensible. Human-written code proportion will drop to single digits. Reasoning models introduced in 2025 with reinforcement learning training will significantly improve code challenge performance. Security issues (particularly sandboxing) will become a core topic.\",\n    45→    \"author\": \"Simon Willison\",\n    46→    \"source\": \"Blog\",\n    47→    \"url\": \"https://www.cnblogs.com/hogwarts/p/19616115\",\n    48→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-20\",\n    49→    \"topics\": [\"LLM code quality\", \"AI predictions\", \"human-AI collaboration\", \"security\", \"reasoning models\"],\n    50→    \"type\": \"opinion\"\n    51→  },\n    52→  {\n    53→    \"title\": \"Simon Willison's Vibe Programming: 17 Minutes, $0.61 to Build Tools\",\n    54→    \"description\": \"Simon Willison shared his experience using Claude Code to build a page showing commit history for his tools. Completed in just over 17 minutes costing only $0.61 in Anthropic API calls. He practices 'vibe programming' - focusing on what the code does while letting LLM handle implementation details. In 2025, he built 110 AI-assisted HTML/JavaScript tools hosted on tools.simonwillison.net.\",\n    55→    \"author\": \"Simon Willison\",\n    56→    \"source\": \"Blog\",\n    57→    \"url\": \"https://www.sohu.com/a/872963913_129720\",\n    58→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-21\",\n    59→    \"topics\": [\"vibe programming\", \"Claude Code\", \"API costs\", \"developer tools\", \"productivity\"],\n    60→    \"type\": \"tutorial\"\n    61→  },\n    62→  {\n    63→    \"title\": \"Replit's Evolution: From Ghostwriter to Agent 3 and Mobile Vibe-Coding\",\n    64→    \"description\": \"Replit, founded by Amjad Masad in 2016, continues evolving its AI-powered development platform. 2022: Launched 'Ghostwriter' AI programming assistant. January 2025: Strategic pivot to focus on cultivating software developers from non-technical backgrounds. September 2025: Released 'Agent 3' tool with autonomous testing and code repair capabilities. January 2026: Launched mobile Vibe-coding functionality for building mobile apps through natural language.\",\n    65→    \"author\": \"Amjad Masad / Replit\",\n    66→    \"source\": \"Tech Media\",\n    67→    \"url\": \"https://baike.baidu.com/item/Replit/64271513\",\n    68→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-21\",\n    69→    \"topics\": [\"Replit\", \"Ghostwriter\", \"Agent 3\", \"mobile development\", \"vibe-coding\", \"AI tools\"],\n    70→    \"type\": \"technical\"\n    71→  },\n    72→  {\n    73→    \"title\": \"Lex Fridman Podcast: DeepSeek Discussion with Sebastian Raschka & Nathan Lambert\",\n    74→    \"description\": \"3+ hour podcast covering 2026 AI industry developments. Topics include RLHF's philosophical challenges, training signal scarcity, DeepSeek's impact on open-source AI, and 'Vibe Coding' - over 25% of senior programmers now have more than half their code AI-generated. Key insight: Future experts won't be those who write code, but those who train AI to write code. Discussion on Silicon Valley work culture at OpenAI and Anthropic.\",\n    75→    \"author\": \"Lex Fridman, Sebastian Raschka, Nathan Lambert\",\n    76→    \"source\": \"Podcast\",\n    77→    \"url\": \"https://www.sohu.com/a/989170238_121124376\",\n    78→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-19\",\n    79→    \"topics\": [\"DeepSeek\", \"RLHF\", \"open-source AI\", \"vibe coding\", \"AI training\", \"work culture\"],\n    80→    \"type\": \"discussion\"\n    81→  },\n    82→  {\n    83→    \"title\": \"Peter Steinberger Interview: OpenClaw and Agent Self-Modification\",\n    84→    \"description\": \"Interview with Peter Steinberger, creator of OpenClaw, about his AI agent that can self-modify code. OpenClaw became GitHub's fastest-growing project with 175K stars as a prototype. Discussion covers Agentic Engineering vs Vibe Coding, AI agents that can modify their own source code, Meta vs OpenAI competition, and the future of software engineering and the app ecosystem. Steinberger joined OpenAI shortly after this interview.\",\n    85→    \"author\": \"Peter Steinberger\",\n    86→    \"source\": \"Podcast / Interview\",\n    87→    \"url\": \"https://m.sohu.com/a/988681156_211762\",\n    88→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-19\",\n    89→    \"topics\": [\"OpenClaw\", \"self-modifying code\", \"agentic engineering\", \"Meta vs OpenAI\", \"AI agents\"],\n    90→    \"type\": \"interview\"\n    91→  },\n    92→  {\n    93→    \"title\": \"Musk's Prediction: AI to Write Binary Code by End of 2026\",\n    94→    \"description\": \"Elon Musk predicted that by the end of 2026, AI would be able to directly write binary code, significantly reducing human dependency on programming languages. This bold claim sparked discussion about the future of programming and whether high-level languages would remain relevant. The prediction was widely covered in Chinese tech media, with debates about its feasibility and implications for software developers.\",\n    95→    \"author\": \"Elon Musk\",\n    96→    \"source\": \"Tech Media\",\n    97→    \"url\": \"https://news.sina.cn/ai/2026-02-19/detail-inhninfq7238545.d.html\",\n    98→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-19\",\n    99→    \"topics\": [\"AI predictions\", \"binary code\", \"future of programming\", \"Musk\", \"code generation\"],\n   100→    \"type\": \"opinion\"\n   101→  },\n   102→  {\n   103→    \"title\": \"Stanford's Vibe Coding Tutorial Released\",\n   104→    \"description\": \"Stanford University released a new tutorial on 'Vibe Coding,' reflecting the growing mainstream acceptance of AI-assisted programming methodologies. The tutorial covers best practices for leveraging LLMs in software development while maintaining code quality and developer understanding. This标志着AI编程方法正式进入学术课程体系。\",\n   105→    \"author\": \"Stanford University\",\n   106→    \"source\": \"Educational\",\n   107→    \"url\": \"https://news.qq.com/rain/a/20260224A06NX300\",\n   108→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-24\",\n   109→    \"topics\": [\"vibe coding\", \"Stanford\", \"AI education\", \"LLM-assisted programming\", \"academic curriculum\"],\n   110→    \"type\": \"tutorial\"\n   111→  },\n   112→  {\n   113→    \"title\": \"AI Programming University Course: 'I've Already Started Learning'\",\n   114→    \"description\": \"News spread about Stanford University offering an AI programming course, generating significant interest in the developer community. The course covers practical AI-assisted development techniques, prompt engineering for code generation, and integrating LLMs into development workflows. This reflects the institutionalization of AI coding skills in formal education.\",\n   115→    \"author\": \"Stanford University / Community\",\n   116→    \"source\": \"Tech Media\",\n   117→    \"url\": \"https://new.qq.com/rain/a/LNK2026022311724900\",\n   118→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-23\",\n   119→    \"topics\": [\"AI education\", \"university courses\", \"programming curriculum\", \"AI-assisted development\"],\n   120→    \"type\": \"tutorial\"\n   121→  },\n   122→  {\n   123→    \"title\": \"Anthropic 2026 Agent Programming Trend Report: Software Development Revolution\",\n   124→    \"description\": \"Anthropic released a comprehensive trend report on AI agent programming, declaring 'the software development revolution has officially arrived.' The report details how AI agents are transforming software engineering, with insights on context engineering, agent autonomy, and the shift from traditional coding to agent orchestration. The report emphasizes that 2026 marks a turning point in AI-assisted software development.\",\n   125→    \"author\": \"Anthropic\",\n   126→    \"source\": \"Tech Report\",\n   127→    \"url\": \"https://new.qq.com/rain/a/20260224A01TEI00\",\n   128→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-24\",\n   129→    \"topics\": [\"Anthropic\", \"AI agents\", \"programming trends\", \"software development revolution\", \"context engineering\"],\n   130→    \"type\": \"technical\"\n   131→  },\n   132→  {\n   133→    \"title\": \"2026 Computer Industry AI Programming Report: New Development Paradigm\",\n   134→    \"description\": \"Industry report on AI programming in 2026 highlights the reshaping of software development paradigms and acceleration of application ecosystem prosperity. The report covers the transition from traditional coding to AI-assisted development, emerging tools and platforms, and predictions for the future of software engineering. Includes analysis of market trends and developer adoption rates.\",\n   135→    \"author\": \"Industry Analysts\",\n   136→    \"source\": \"Industry Report\",\n   137→    \"url\": \"https://m.sohu.com/a/988727666_121123901/?pvid=000115_3w_a\",\n   138→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-24\",\n   139→    \"topics\": [\"AI programming\", \"industry trends\", \"development paradigms\", \"market analysis\", \"adoption rates\"],\n   140→    \"type\": \"technical\"\n   141→  },\n   142→  {\n   143→    \"title\": \"Claude Code GitHub Integration: Multi-Language Support and Cross-Platform Sync\",\n   144→    \"description\": \"GitHub Copilot's 2026 features expanded to include multi-language support (Rust, Go) and cross-platform synchronization. Integration with Claude Code workflows became more seamless, allowing developers to use AI assistance across different projects and platforms. Coverage of Claude Code's integration with GitHub for enhanced AI-assisted development workflows.\",\n   145→    \"author\": \"GitHub / Anthropic\",\n   146→    \"source\": \"Tech Media\",\n   147→    \"url\": \"https://m.blog.csdn.net/weixin_44387393/article/details/153180817\",\n   148→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-20\",\n   149→    \"topics\": [\"Claude Code\", \"GitHub\", \"multi-language support\", \"cross-platform\", \"AI integration\"],\n   150→    \"type\": \"technical\"\n   151→  },\n   152→  {\n   153→    \"title\": \"AI Developer Day: Microsoft's Focus on Azure, GitHub, and AI-Powered Coding Quality\",\n   154→    \"description\": \"Microsoft held AI Developer Day events focusing on Azure, GitHub, and AI-powered coding quality improvements. The events showcased Microsoft's vision for AI-assisted development, including new tools, APIs, and best practices for integrating AI into development workflows. Emphasis on enterprise adoption and production-quality AI-generated code.\",\n   155→    \"author\": \"Microsoft\",\n   156→    \"source\": \"Tech Event\",\n   157→    \"url\": \"https://developer.microsoft.com/reactor/series/s-1616/?wt.mc_id=organic_S-1612_organicsocial_reactor\",\n   158→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-21\",\n   159→    \"topics\": [\"Microsoft\", \"Azure\", \"GitHub\", \"AI development\", \"enterprise tools\", \"code quality\"],\n   160→    \"type\": \"technical\"\n   161→  },\n   162→  {\n   163→    \"title\": \"Context Engineering: The First Priority in AI Agent Development\",\n   164→    \"description\": \"Emerging consensus that 'Context Engineering' is the critical skill for AI agent development. Articles and discussions emphasized that managing context windows, prompt construction, and information retrieval are more important than traditional coding skills. This shift represents a fundamental change in what it means to be a software developer in the AI era.\",\n   165→    \"author\": \"Various Thought Leaders\",\n   166→    \"source\": \"Technical Blog\",\n   167→    \"url\": \"https://m.toutiao.com/a7609923921042817576/\",\n   168→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-23\",\n   169→    \"topics\": [\"context engineering\", \"AI agents\", \"prompt engineering\", \"developer skills\", \"context windows\"],\n   170→    \"type\": \"technical\"\n   171→  },\n   172→  {\n   173→    \"title\": \"Awesome AI Coding: Comprehensive Resource Navigation\",\n   174→    \"description\": \"The 'Awesome AI Coding' project gained attention as a comprehensive resource for AI programming tools and frameworks. The curated list includes code generation tools, LLM-based development environments, agent frameworks, and educational resources. This reflects the exploding ecosystem of AI coding tools and the need for organized navigation of the landscape.\",\n   175→    \"author\": \"Community Contributors\",\n   176→    \"source\": \"GitHub / Community\",\n   177→    \"url\": \"https://juejin.cn/post/7607589189265997862\",\n   178→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-22\",\n   179→    \"topics\": [\"AI tools\", \"resource navigation\", \"developer resources\", \"open source\", \"tooling ecosystem\"],\n   180→    \"type\": \"technical\"\n   181→  },\n   182→  {\n   183→    \"title\": \"8 Popular AI Programming Tools Comparison for 2026\",\n   184→    \"description\": \"Comprehensive comparison of 8 popular AI coding tools for 2026, including CodeLlama, Claude Code, Cursor, Devin, GitHub Copilot, and others. The analysis covers features, pricing, performance, and use cases for each tool. Developers now face a rich ecosystem of AI-assisted development options, each with different strengths and specializations.\",\n   185→    \"author\": \"Tech Reviewers\",\n   186→    \"source\": \"Tech Media\",\n   187→    \"url\": \"https://m.toutiao.com/a7610401873857692179/\",\n   188→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-23\",\n   189→    \"topics\": [\"AI tools\", \"comparison\", \"CodeLlama\", \"Claude Code\", \"Cursor\", \"Devin\", \"GitHub Copilot\"],\n   190→    \"type\": \"technical\"\n   191→  },\n   192→  {\n   193→    \"title\": \"AI Coding Not So Magical: 22 Developers Reveal Real Impact and Challenges\",\n   194→    \"description\": \"Survey of 22 software developers revealed the real impact and challenges of AI coding tools. While productivity gains are significant, developers also experience skill degradation, over-reliance on AI, and concerns about code quality. The study highlights that AI coding is a 'double-edged sword' - improving efficiency while potentially eroding fundamental programming skills.\",\n   195→    \"author\": \"Developer Community\",\n   196→    \"source\": \"Survey / Research\",\n   197→    \"url\": \"https://m.sohu.com/a/954206809_122362510/?pvid=000115_3w_a\",\n   198→    \"published_date\": \"2026-02-20\",\n   199→    \"topics\": [\"AI coding challenges\", \"developer survey\", \"skill degradation\", \"productivity\", \"code quality\"],\n   200→    \"type\": \"discussion\"\n   201→  }\n   202→]\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"
      }
